Model 1 is best. By playing 1…Rg8–g1# Black immediately delivers a back‐rank mate: the rook on g1 attacks the king along the first rank (f1–e1–d1–c1–b1), and  
• a1 is covered by the pawn on b2  
• c1 is covered by the new rook on g1  
• c2 is covered by White’s own bishop on b3  
• b2 is occupied by Black’s pawn  
so White’s king on b1 has no legal escape. None of the other suggested moves wins on the spot.
